{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/nubank/credit-card-design","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h3 id=\"joining-credit-card\" style=\"position:relative;\">Joining credit card<a href=\"#joining-credit-card\" aria-label=\"joining credit card permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>When I joined Nubank, my interest for human behaviour, business, data models and the dry access to credit in my home country swiftly drew me to our core product: the credit card.</p>\n<p>Back then, designers were focused on shipping new products and I was excited to push our core product to the next level.</p>\n<h3 id=\"embracing-leadership\" style=\"position:relative;\">Embracing leadership<a href=\"#embracing-leadership\" aria-label=\"embracing leadership permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>As the company jumped into hypergrowth, it was clear Nubank required more design leaders. I stepped up and was fortunate to help build this team from the ground up.</p>\n<p>Credit card has been my home at Nubank for the past 3 years and the best team of product designers, user researchers and content strategists I have ever worked with.</p>\n<!-- |   |   |\n|---|---|\n|<h5>Diego Vieira, Product Designer</h5>|Amanda Elyss, Product Designer|\n|Mariana Medina, UX Writer|Leticia Ratkiewicz, UX Researcher|\n|Ricardo Perotti, UX Researcher|Williams Oliveira, Product Designer|\n|Rafael Rozendo, Product Designer|Ana Menezes, Product Designer|\n|Andre Mooij, Product Designer|Renato Souza, Product Designer|\n|Amanda Legge, Design Manager - Consumer Lending| | -->\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 940px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 40%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Credit Card Design team, Dec. 2020\"\n        title=\"Credit Card Design team, Dec. 2020\"\n        src=\"/static/6275301b4e6682ba1c1c9666191c5b7d/7ef15/credit-card-design-team-2.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6275301b4e6682ba1c1c9666191c5b7d/6c4e6/credit-card-design-team-2.png 235w,\n/static/6275301b4e6682ba1c1c9666191c5b7d/f9c87/credit-card-design-team-2.png 470w,\n/static/6275301b4e6682ba1c1c9666191c5b7d/7ef15/credit-card-design-team-2.png 940w,\n/static/6275301b4e6682ba1c1c9666191c5b7d/77c84/credit-card-design-team-2.png 1410w,\n/static/6275301b4e6682ba1c1c9666191c5b7d/0b3f2/credit-card-design-team-2.png 1607w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\"><p>Credit Card Design team, Dec. 2020</p></figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<!-- Iougo Huan, Product Designer -->\n<!-- ### Team Impact -->\n<!-- LT: Early suggestions on how to interview designers (shared with Egon) -->\n<!-- Ana Mê, Rafa, Polyana: Structure our Design Days\nWilliams: loading screen states -->\n<!-- Amanda Elyss: boleto payment + Critique Queen -->\n<!-- Diego and Amanda Legge: Ultravioleta -->\n<!-- Leticia and I: Mapping user needs and product opportunities for the Business Unit + Presenting our process at UXRConf 2020 -->\n<!-- Rafael Rozendo: Secured Lines/Card -->\n<!-- Andre Mooij: Launching México\nAna Mê: Collecting debt -->\n<h3 id=\"impact\" style=\"position:relative;\">Impact<a href=\"#impact\" aria-label=\"impact permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>Our main accomplishments have been to:</p>\n<div style=\"display:flex-center; margin-top:1rem;\"> \n\t<div style=\"background-color:var(--bg-light); padding: 16px; border-radius:3px;margin:0 0 16px 0 ;flex-grow: 1;width: auto;\">\n\t\t<h3 style=\"margin-top:0\"><strong>1</strong></h3>\n        <h3 style=\"margin-top:0\"><strong>Build a strong design team</strong></h3>\n\t\t<p>Always ready to help each other grow in their careers</p>\n\t</div>\n    <div style=\"background-color:var(--bg-light); padding: 16px; border-radius:3px;margin:0 0 16px 0 ;flex-grow: 1;width: auto;\">\n\t\t<h3 style=\"margin-top:0\"><strong>2</strong></h3>\n        <a href=\"/nubank/credit-card-design/#2-outlining-our-vision-of-the-future\">\n\t\t\t<h3 style=\"margin-top:0\"><strong>Outline our vision of the future</strong></h3>\n\t\t</a>\n\t\t<p>Keeping Brazilians' favourite credit card always fresh and meaningful to them</p>\n\t</div>\n    <div style=\"background-color:var(--bg-light); padding: 16px; border-radius:3px;margin:0 8px 0 0 ;flex-grow: 1;width: auto; margin: auto\">\n\t\t<h3 style=\"margin-top:0\"><strong>3</strong></h3>\n        <h3 style=\"margin-top:0\"><strong>Foster a trusting and collaborative environment</strong></h3>\n\t\t<p>For both designers and our cross-functional partners.</p>\n\t</div>\n\t<div style=\"background-color:var(--bg-lightest); padding: 16px; border-radius:3px;margin:0 0 0 8px;flex-grow: 1; width: calc(50% - 8px)\">\n\t</div>\n</div>\n<br>\n<p>Let’s dive into each of these areas and some of the work done behind each of them. As with any great band, these were a group effort and not my accomplish alone.</p>\n<p>I’m proud of how we optimised our team for autonomy and collaboration, making this is a collective story of success. I’ll try to cover the surface, but don’t hesitate to <a href=\"mailto:hey@lucasterra.com?subject=Building a Design Team\">reach out</a> if you’d like to learn more.</p>\n<br>\n<br>\n<hr>\n<br>\n<br>\n<h2 id=\"1-building-a-strong-design-team\" style=\"position:relative;\">1. Building a strong design team<a href=\"#1-building-a-strong-design-team\" aria-label=\"1 building a strong design team permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 940px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 74.8936170212766%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"A daily sync from the early days of our team · with Diego, Leticia and Egon\"\n        title=\"A daily sync from the early days of our team · with Diego, Leticia and Egon\"\n        src=\"/static/4130ac7d9208d3a5e055fbc1d4c595ef/f06fb/Daily-sync-from-when-we-were-a-small-team.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4130ac7d9208d3a5e055fbc1d4c595ef/5d189/Daily-sync-from-when-we-were-a-small-team.jpg 235w,\n/static/4130ac7d9208d3a5e055fbc1d4c595ef/7d6cd/Daily-sync-from-when-we-were-a-small-team.jpg 470w,\n/static/4130ac7d9208d3a5e055fbc1d4c595ef/f06fb/Daily-sync-from-when-we-were-a-small-team.jpg 940w,\n/static/4130ac7d9208d3a5e055fbc1d4c595ef/c75e4/Daily-sync-from-when-we-were-a-small-team.jpg 1410w,\n/static/4130ac7d9208d3a5e055fbc1d4c595ef/0dd9a/Daily-sync-from-when-we-were-a-small-team.jpg 1880w,\n/static/4130ac7d9208d3a5e055fbc1d4c595ef/05366/Daily-sync-from-when-we-were-a-small-team.jpg 3264w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\"><p>A daily sync from the early days of our team · with Diego, Leticia and Egon</p></figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<h3 id=\"finding-the-right-people\" style=\"position:relative;\">Finding the right people<a href=\"#finding-the-right-people\" aria-label=\"finding the right people permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>In 2018, Nubank hit puberty and was starting to grow fast. As with any adolescent, different parts of the body grew faster than others. Design was one that took longer to develop.</p>\n<p>The first three people I helped hire (in the picture above) were two product designers and a UX researcher. We all had a very complementary set of personalities, backgrounds and technical skills — which added a ton whenever we seeked a different perspective on the problems we had at hand.</p>\n<p>We matched our gradient of skills and personal interests with specific moments of people’s journey with their credit cards. For example: Diego’s deep apreciation for details and visual design made him the perfect candidate to lead design for our rewards program. My interest in data and business led me to stay closer to how our limit increase policies should work.</p>\n<p>A few months in and it was now their time to also help find the best talent our there, so I shared my thoughts and learnings from interviewing design candidates.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 940px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 54.46808510638298%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Personal notes and tips for phone screening candidates. Shared with early members of the team.\"\n        title=\"Personal notes and tips for phone screening candidates. Shared with early members of the team.\"\n        src=\"/static/dc4e212d15bae4eb385a91a0ae605cc1/7ef15/Notes-on-phone-screenings-by-Lucas-Terra.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/dc4e212d15bae4eb385a91a0ae605cc1/6c4e6/Notes-on-phone-screenings-by-Lucas-Terra.png 235w,\n/static/dc4e212d15bae4eb385a91a0ae605cc1/f9c87/Notes-on-phone-screenings-by-Lucas-Terra.png 470w,\n/static/dc4e212d15bae4eb385a91a0ae605cc1/7ef15/Notes-on-phone-screenings-by-Lucas-Terra.png 940w,\n/static/dc4e212d15bae4eb385a91a0ae605cc1/77c84/Notes-on-phone-screenings-by-Lucas-Terra.png 1410w,\n/static/dc4e212d15bae4eb385a91a0ae605cc1/1be2d/Notes-on-phone-screenings-by-Lucas-Terra.png 1880w,\n/static/dc4e212d15bae4eb385a91a0ae605cc1/29ab1/Notes-on-phone-screenings-by-Lucas-Terra.png 2842w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\"><p>Personal notes and tips for phone screening candidates. Shared with early members of the team.</p></figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<h3 id=\"evolving-our-rituals\" style=\"position:relative;\">Evolving our rituals<a href=\"#evolving-our-rituals\" aria-label=\"evolving our rituals permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>In 2019 the team had doubled in size (around 6 people) and our rituals evolved a ton. We started sharing some of the housekeeping tasks so everybody was a leader in one direction. Diego and Ana, for example took over our team retrospectives and Amanda was nominated the “queen of design critiques”, helping team members ensure they were getting the most out of their design crits.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 940px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 74.8936170212766%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Co-designing a better UI for the transaction feed · with Amanda, Diego, Ana\"\n        title=\"Co-designing a better UI for the transaction feed · with Amanda, Diego, Ana\"\n        src=\"/static/7932cfdd05fc408a06613fedc275aad5/f06fb/co--design.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/7932cfdd05fc408a06613fedc275aad5/5d189/co--design.jpg 235w,\n/static/7932cfdd05fc408a06613fedc275aad5/7d6cd/co--design.jpg 470w,\n/static/7932cfdd05fc408a06613fedc275aad5/f06fb/co--design.jpg 940w,\n/static/7932cfdd05fc408a06613fedc275aad5/c75e4/co--design.jpg 1410w,\n/static/7932cfdd05fc408a06613fedc275aad5/0dd9a/co--design.jpg 1880w,\n/static/7932cfdd05fc408a06613fedc275aad5/f8b09/co--design.jpg 4032w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\"><p>Co-designing a better UI for the transaction feed · with Amanda, Diego, Ana</p></figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<h3 id=\"working-remote\" style=\"position:relative;\">Working remote<a href=\"#working-remote\" aria-label=\"working remote permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>More recently, during a team retrospective amidst the pandemic, we all brought up how we were struggling with calendar tetris, making space for collaboration and getting to know new team members. Ana, Rafa and Poly volunteer to tackle the problem and after a couple of discussions and feedback from the entire team organized a virtual “Design Studio Day” block on Thursdays. We now have a moment of the week to gather feedback, learn more about the other projects happening and get to know one another.</p>\n<p>We usually stay connected on Discord where there are different rooms for different purposes (pick right one if you’re looking for feedback). The agenda for the day varies depending on the week of the month. </p>\n<p>Growing a cohesive, connected and empowered team takes time. The integration and collaboration that comes from spending Thursdays together as a team has really paid off — especially over such a long period working from home.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 940px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 56.17021276595745%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Design Day agenda · by Ana, Poly and Rafa\"\n        title=\"Design Day agenda · by Ana, Poly and Rafa\"\n        src=\"/static/4c4355256f8d4e5dcd6ff1a9627d435d/7ef15/Remote-Design-Studio-Day.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4c4355256f8d4e5dcd6ff1a9627d435d/6c4e6/Remote-Design-Studio-Day.png 235w,\n/static/4c4355256f8d4e5dcd6ff1a9627d435d/f9c87/Remote-Design-Studio-Day.png 470w,\n/static/4c4355256f8d4e5dcd6ff1a9627d435d/7ef15/Remote-Design-Studio-Day.png 940w,\n/static/4c4355256f8d4e5dcd6ff1a9627d435d/77c84/Remote-Design-Studio-Day.png 1410w,\n/static/4c4355256f8d4e5dcd6ff1a9627d435d/1be2d/Remote-Design-Studio-Day.png 1880w,\n/static/4c4355256f8d4e5dcd6ff1a9627d435d/a4b11/Remote-Design-Studio-Day.png 2560w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\"><p>Design Day agenda · by Ana, Poly and Rafa</p></figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<!-- \n- Supporting each other on the development of our careers, by Leticia and I at UXR conf -->\n<br>\n<br>\n<!-- <blockquote style=\" flex-grow: 1;\"> \n    <div style=\"\">\n        <h2 style=\"margin-top:.75rem; margin-bottom:.45rem\"><strong>2. Outlining our vision of the future</strong></h2>\n\t\t<p>Keeping the our customer's credit card always fresh and meaningful to them</p>\n\t</div>\n</div></blockquote>\n<br> -->\n<h2 id=\"2-outlining-our-vision-of-the-future\" style=\"position:relative;\">2. Outlining our vision of the future<a href=\"#2-outlining-our-vision-of-the-future\" aria-label=\"2 outlining our vision of the future permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p><strong>While our vision of the future will always remain confidential, here are some of the bits pushing us into the right direction.</strong></p>\n<h3 id=\"spreading-out-the-nu-magic\" style=\"position:relative;\">Spreading out the Nu magic<a href=\"#spreading-out-the-nu-magic\" aria-label=\"spreading out the nu magic permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>Nubank originally surprised customers with the level of thought and attention to critical moments. We stand out in the crowd for how we deal with bad experiences with our service. We excel at what other companies would see as “edge cases” — these are usually the most critical moments people have with your product, so we want to get them right.</p>\n<p><em>Ana worked on a flow that empowers users to create agreements to pay off debt in the app, increasing by 20% the number of “healed” customers.</em></p>\n<!-- ![Pay off debt in the app · by Ana](/images/Collections-Agreements-in-app-by-Ana-2.gif) -->\n<img src=\"/99876943c8bdce3c22bc3d2546709e9b/huge_Ana.gif\" alt=\"Pay off debt in the app · by Ana\">\n<h5>Pay off debt, a new feature that increased in 20% · by Ana</h5>\n<!-- Williams also covers a number of edge\n\n![Limit adjust screen, now covering  · by Williams]() -->\n<h3 id=\"being-respectful-and-transparent-about-how-we-use-customer-data\" style=\"position:relative;\">Being respectful and transparent about how we use customer data<a href=\"#being-respectful-and-transparent-about-how-we-use-customer-data\" aria-label=\"being respectful and transparent about how we use customer data permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>Credit analysis is known for coming across as a total enigma. <em>Williams optimised the loading states in our app to be more transparent and educative about how we use customer data</em> in their credit analysis. This has had an impact in customer behaviour and also increased the limit utilization for customers who saw these loading states.</p>\n<p>This pattern is now the new standard across the company as we persist on our fight against complexity.</p>\n<!-- ![New loading state pattern introduced by Williams](/images/New-loading-pattern-by-Williams.gif) -->\n<img src=\"/70b028aa968caa49f229eb4077dd8bfb/hugeWill.gif\" alt=\"New loading state pattern introduced by Williams\">\n<h3 id=\"adapting-to-customers-needs-during-the-pandemic\" style=\"position:relative;\">Adapting to customers needs during the pandemic<a href=\"#adapting-to-customers-needs-during-the-pandemic\" aria-label=\"adapting to customers needs during the pandemic permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>The covid crisis in 2020 hit the whole world in many unexpected ways. In Brazil alone, over 8.9 million people lost their jobs from January to March. Out of the many improvements Amanda did in our app, offering better refinancing options and creating a hub for donations were the ones that helped both customers and Nubank get to the other side of this together.</p>\n<img src=\"\" alt=\"Better financing options · by Amanda\">\n<img src=\"\" alt=\"Twitter comments\">\n<h3 id=\"expanding-into-new-geographies\" style=\"position:relative;\">Expanding into new geographies<a href=\"#expanding-into-new-geographies\" aria-label=\"expanding into new geographies permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>In 2019, Andre joined as our first designer in Mexico and in 2020, Santiago as the first designer in Colombia. In both countries, Credit Card was the first product we launched.</p>\n<p>They have worked hard into expanding the frontiers of our product, originally designed for the Brazilian market, and translated and redesigned the experience so that it attends both user and regulator needs in our new markets. At the time of this writing, in December 2020 there are now X customers in Mexico and Y customers in our Colombia waitlist.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 940px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 68.93617021276596%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Mexico and Colombia Launch · by Andre, Veronica, Esmeralda, Omar, Santiago, Claudio, and several others\"\n        title=\"Mexico and Colombia Launch · by Andre, Veronica, Esmeralda, Omar, Santiago, Claudio, and several others\"\n        src=\"/static/2e631b7e690349f6acc120a40e226e12/7ef15/Nubank-MX.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/2e631b7e690349f6acc120a40e226e12/6c4e6/Nubank-MX.png 235w,\n/static/2e631b7e690349f6acc120a40e226e12/f9c87/Nubank-MX.png 470w,\n/static/2e631b7e690349f6acc120a40e226e12/7ef15/Nubank-MX.png 940w,\n/static/2e631b7e690349f6acc120a40e226e12/77c84/Nubank-MX.png 1410w,\n/static/2e631b7e690349f6acc120a40e226e12/a29a0/Nubank-MX.png 1786w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\"><p>Mexico and Colombia Launch · by Andre, Veronica, Esmeralda, Omar, Santiago, Claudio, and several others</p></figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<h3 id=\"helping-the-next-50mm-customers-build-their-path-to-credit\" style=\"position:relative;\">Helping the next 50MM customers build their path to credit<a href=\"#helping-the-next-50mm-customers-build-their-path-to-credit\" aria-label=\"helping the next 50mm customers build their path to credit permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>Due to the huge success of our credit card, since mid-2019 a good chunk of my attention has been dedicated to finding new ways of offering credit options. We’re now slowly rolling out a program that is expected to help over 50 million Brazilians (re)build credit.</p>\n<img src=\"\" alt=\"Credit Building program · with Rafael\">\n<!-- ### Hitting refresh in our rewards program\n- Ultravioleta, led by Amanda Legge and Diego Vieira -->\n<br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<h2 id=\"3-fostering-trust-and-collaboration-with-our-partners\" style=\"position:relative;\">3. Fostering trust and collaboration with our partners<a href=\"#3-fostering-trust-and-collaboration-with-our-partners\" aria-label=\"3 fostering trust and collaboration with our partners permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<!-- \nWithin our design team, there are a couple of rituals that \n1. Creative sessions are a reserved space of the week where designers can decide to run a design critique, a team discussion, \n2. Team retros are for oiling up the engines. They're usually facilitated by Diego, who also excells at designing spreadsheets such as this one -->\n<h3 id=\"mixing-multiple-views-on-customer-understanding\" style=\"position:relative;\">Mixing multiple views on customer understanding<a href=\"#mixing-multiple-views-on-customer-understanding\" aria-label=\"mixing multiple views on customer understanding permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>Soon after Leticia joined, we kicked off a foundational research initiative in partnership with data scientists in the team. </p>\n<p>We used existing data to segment our ever growing customer base into smaller, more actionable and measurable buckets of behaviour, that guided the product strategy and . We were invited to present our method at <a href=\"https://uxrconf.com\">UXR Conf</a>.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 940px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 74.8936170212766%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Leticia and I presenting the work we did in partnership with data scientsts at UXR Conf\"\n        title=\"Leticia and I presenting the work we did in partnership with data scientsts at UXR Conf\"\n        src=\"/static/a52add830963a55dc1fef2660c974c24/f06fb/Presenting-our-Research-method-at-UXR-Conf.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/a52add830963a55dc1fef2660c974c24/5d189/Presenting-our-Research-method-at-UXR-Conf.jpg 235w,\n/static/a52add830963a55dc1fef2660c974c24/7d6cd/Presenting-our-Research-method-at-UXR-Conf.jpg 470w,\n/static/a52add830963a55dc1fef2660c974c24/f06fb/Presenting-our-Research-method-at-UXR-Conf.jpg 940w,\n/static/a52add830963a55dc1fef2660c974c24/533d0/Presenting-our-Research-method-at-UXR-Conf.jpg 1280w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\"><p>Leticia and I presenting the work we did in partnership with data scientsts at UXR Conf</p></figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<h3 id=\"keeping-the-different-parts-of-the-product-connected\" style=\"position:relative;\">Keeping the different parts of the product connected<a href=\"#keeping-the-different-parts-of-the-product-connected\" aria-label=\"keeping the different parts of the product connected permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>Product weekly meetings (PM, PMM, Design, Research, GM)</p>\n<img src=\"\">\n<h3 id=\"co-designing-solutions-with-our-peers\" style=\"position:relative;\">Co-designing solutions with our peers<a href=\"#co-designing-solutions-with-our-peers\" aria-label=\"co designing solutions with our peers permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>Trabalhando junto com BAs, PMs, etc</p>\n<img src=\"\" alt=\"Chargeback team ideating with customer support\">\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"peer-feedback\" style=\"position:relative;\">Peer Feedback<a href=\"#peer-feedback\" aria-label=\"peer feedback permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>Things people told me that get me energized to do my best work.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Not only you inspire designers, but PMs also reach out to you to get inputs on the mechanisms behind the scenes and discuss ideas and strategies. You’re a true partner and always demonstrate genuine care for our customers.</strong>\n<br><br>— Mariana Penido, Head of Product for Credit Card</p>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Credit card is the most innovative team at Nubank. You found a way to articulate how design makes an impact in the business that I would love to replicate. I can see the team has been successful at constantly questioning what has been held true/ worked well in the past.</strong> <br><br> — Renata Veiga, Design Manager for Lending</p>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>To me it’s 100% clear Lucas doesn’t work for the Credit Card business unit but for our customers. And he knows how to go all the way back to tell how these decisions have an impact on the business.</strong>\n<br><br>— Luiza Ferraz, Product Marketing Manager</p>\n</blockquote>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"customer-feedback\" style=\"position:relative;\">Customer feedback<a href=\"#customer-feedback\" aria-label=\"customer feedback permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>Add social media stuff</p>","frontmatter":{"path":"/nubank/credit-ca